HEADWORD: Cessavit
<hw>Ces*sa"vit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., he has
ceased.]</ety> <mark>[O. Eng. Law]</mark> <def>A writ given by statute
to recover lands when the tenant has for two years failed to perform the
conditions of his tenure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

